be.kdg.se3.services

Class LicensePlateServiceProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.kdg.se3.services.LicensePlateServiceProxy

  • public class LicensePlateServiceProxy
extends java.lang.Object
    Proxy that simulates a call to the license plate service
    The proxy mimics the real HTTP service as close as possible: it is called with a URL and returns JSON
    The URL does not exist and no real HTTP call is made; the proxy just holds the calling thread for some millis to simulate network latency
    A call to www.services4se3.com/license-plate/plateId will return a JSON with info on the plate with the specified id (int)
    The JSON response has the following structure

    {
    plateId: the id of the plate that was requested (string) ,
    nationalNumber: the nation number of the owner of the vehicle (string) ,
    euroNorm: the euronorm of the vehicle (int)
    }



    All plateId's are supposed to be 9 chars long, no further checks are done
    The service returns data in realistic ranges, but the data is random generated so subsequent calls with the same id will return in most cases different data
    Some id's return not random but always the same data:
    - plateId '1-ABC-123' returns a euroNorm of 1
    - plateId '2-ABC-123' returns a euroNorm of 2
    - plateId '3-ABC-123' returns a euroNorm of 3
    - plateId '4-ABC-123' returns a euroNorm of 4
    - plateId '1-ERR-123' will always raise an IOException to simulate a communication error
    - plateId '2-ERR-123' will raise in half of the cases an IOException to simulate a communication error
    - plateId '1-UNK-123' will return an UnknownPlateId error response (see below)
    - plateId's not 9 char's long will return an error JSON response (see below) indicating an invalid camera id
    - an incorrect URL will raise an IOException

    An error JSON response indicates that the call succeeded but no sensible data could be returned. It has the following format
    {
    error: the type of error: InvalidPlateId or UnknownPlateId (string),
    description: a description of the error (string)
    }
